---
/**
 * Why this matters — three positions reflecting the new framing:
 * replacing both the consultant and the overpriced legacy software,
 * with AI used to clear infrastructure friction (not as marketing).
 */
import '../styles/why.css';
---
<section class="why" id="how">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <div class="why-stat">
      <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <rect x="4.5" y="6" width="10" height="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <rect x="9.5" y="12" width="10" height="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <path d="M3.5 19L20.5 5" stroke="#F0A91A" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="butt"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
      <p class="why-stat__num">01</p>
      <p class="why-stat__k">Replaces the consultant <span class="why-stat__amp">and</span> the overpriced software.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Run an impact study yourself, on your own data, when the question gets asked, instead of waiting three weeks for an outside firm or paying six figures for a license.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-stat">
      <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <path d="M4 18L4 14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M9 18L9 10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M14 18L14 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M19 18L19 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M3 20L20.5 20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <circle cx="14" cy="6" r="1.5" fill="#F0A91A"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
      <p class="why-stat__num">02</p>
      <p class="why-stat__k">Real-time data your team already has.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Administrative records, payroll detail, and high-frequency public sources, not national averages from a 2017 input-output table.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-stat">
      <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <path d="M12 4L12 9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M12 15L12 20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M4 12L9 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M15 12L20 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M6.5 6.5L9.75 9.75" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M14.25 14.25L17.5 17.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M17.5 6.5L14.25 9.75" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <path d="M9.75 14.25L6.5 17.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1.75" fill="currentColor"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
      <p class="why-stat__num">03</p>
      <p class="why-stat__k">AI we built in to do the unglamorous work.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Cedar reads messy uploads across departments, flags every assumption the model is about to use, and writes the source record. Used to reduce the infrastructure that slows analysis down, not as a marketing badge.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
